OL,3,CWoman's pension payments stopped for
OL,4,Cmonths after HMRC told her she was dead
OL,6,FThe letter read: "I'm sorry to hear of
OL,7,Fyour recent bereavement and I
OL,8,Frecognise this is a difficult time for
OL,9,Fyou".
OL,11,FElizabeth's son-in-law Dave Crabtree
OL,12,Fsaid: "It came as a little bit of a
OL,13,Fshock to say the least, seeing as
OL,14,Fshe's alive and kicking."
OL,16,FOn the same day she received a bank
OL,17,Fstatement that showed her pension
OL,18,Fpayment had not been made.
